# http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000028
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000028> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000028> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000030> .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000028> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112> "a serial number such as \"12324X\""@en .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000028> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112> "a stop sign"@en .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000028> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112> "a written proper name such as \"OBI\""@en .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000028> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "An information content entity that is a mark(s) or character(s) used as a conventional representation of another entity."@en .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000028> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> "20091104, MC: this needs work and will most probably change"@en .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000028> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> "2014-03-31: We would like to have a deeper analysis of 'mark' and 'sign' in the future (see https://github.com/information-artifact-ontology/IAO/issues/154)."@en .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000028> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> "based on Oxford English Dictionary"@en .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000028> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "symbol"@en .
