<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001003> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001003> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "collaboration"@en .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001003> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A collaboration is a process in which multiple entities, such as individuals, organizations, or institutions, work together toward shared goals, contributing resources, expertise, or services to achieve mutual benefits." .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001003> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#editorialNote> "HBN: Concerning the content of ‘International Collaboration’ datasheet and its related knowledge graph, the ‘Collaboration’ class and its subclasses were created to defind the type of collaborations, and respond to competency questions like: what type of collaboration exists between organizations A and B, which agents are involved in collaboration C, which collaborations has agent D, etc." .
# 
# http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001004
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001004> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001004> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001003> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001004> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "strategic collaboration"@en .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001004> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Strategic Collaboration is a collaboration process in which multiple entities align their long-term objectives and resources to achieve significant mutual benefits in research, business, or policy initiatives." .
# 
# http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001005
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001005> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001005> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001003> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001005> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "networking"@en .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001005> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Networking is a collaboration process that involves building and maintaining professional, academic, or organizational relationships to exchange knowledge, expertise, or resources." .
# 
# http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001006
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001006> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001006> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001003> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001006> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "project collaboration"@en .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001006> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Project Collaboration is a collaboration process in which multiple entities contribute expertise, resources, and labor toward the successful completion of a specific project." .
# 
# http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001007
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001007> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001007> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001003> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001007> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "joint efforting"@en .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001007> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Joint Efforting is a collaboration process in which multiple entities combine efforts, knowledge, or labor toward a common goal, often in research, policy-making, or community initiatives." .
# 
# http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001008
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001008> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001008> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001003> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001008> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "joint servicing"@en .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001008> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Joint Servicing is a collaboration process in which two or more entities jointly provide or maintain a service, ensuring operational efficiency and shared responsibility." .
# 
# http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001009
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001009> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001009> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001003> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001009> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "alliancing"@en .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001009> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Alliancing is a collaboration process in which two or more entities form a long-term cooperative relationship based on shared objectives, often in research, industry, or government sectors." .
# 
# http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001010
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001010> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001010> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001003> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001010> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "parenting"@en .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001010> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Partnering is a collaboration process in which two or more entities form a structured partnership to achieve specific research, business, or development goals." .
# 
# http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001012
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001012> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
