<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001051> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "implementing process"@en .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001051> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A process that applies, integrates, or refines an entity, encompassing development, co-development, and adaptation, with participant involvement to achieve a functional outcome." .
# 
# http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001055
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001055> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001055> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000229> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001055> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "research group role"@en .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001055> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Research group role is an agent role that is borne by an organizational unit and is realized through conducting, coordinating, or supporting scientific research activities within one or more research domains." .
# 
# http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001056
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001056> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001056> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> "https://doi.org/10.1016/j.actamat.2025.120735" .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001056> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0100001> <https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0001203> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001056> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A Reference Dataset is a dataset that serves as a benchmark or standardized collection of data used for validation, comparison, and reproducibility in scientific research and engineering applications." .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001056> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Reference data of materials\n- are documented according to certain standards as well as\n- are curated (i.e., generated, maintained, preserved, validated) according to certain standards\n- are quantitative data sets (i.e., data + their corresponding metadata)\n- have been measured or simulated to a particularly high standard, and\n- are generated for a material that has either experienced a well-documented process or is reference material\nor its composition and structure has been completely characterized.\nReference data of materials can also be derived data from reference data.\nThese data are distributed with a license (e.g., GPL).\nThe here addressed standards for documentation, curation and measurement need to be defined for specific\nmaterials characteristics (e.g., creep tests) in terms of domain standards. These domain standards are the\nresult of a steered community process.\nStandards should integrate as much as possible existing standards (e.g., the individual MatWerk domain\nstandards should be as much as possible consistent)." .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001056> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "obsolete reference dataset"@en .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001056> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#deprecated> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001056> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "BAM reference data: results of ASTM E139 -11 creep tests on a reference material of Nimonic 75 nickel-base alloy (https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7764161)" .
# 
# http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001057
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001057> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001057> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0100001> <https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0001205> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001057> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A Simulation Dataset is a dataset that contains data generated from computational models, numerical simulations, or digital twin environments to predict material behaviors, properties, and interactions." .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001057> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "obsolete simulation dataset"@en .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001057> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#deprecated> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001057> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Examples include DFT simulation datasets, molecular dynamics (MD) trajectory files, and phase-field modeling results." .
# 
# http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001058
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001058> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001058> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0100001> <https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0001203> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001058> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An Experimental Dataset is a dataset that contains measured or observed data collected from laboratory experiments, physical tests, or scientific investigations." .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001058> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "obsolete experimental dataset"@en .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001058> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#deprecated> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
# 
# http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001059
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001059> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001059> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0100001> <https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0001209> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001059> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A Journal Article is a peer-reviewed scholarly publication that presents original research, review studies, or theoretical discussions, typically published in academic journals." .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001059> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "obsolete journal article"@en .
