<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001060> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A SPARQL Endpoint is a web application software that provides a queryable interface for accessing and retrieving structured data from RDF-based knowledge graphs using the SPARQL query language." .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001060> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "obsolete sparql endpoint"@en .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001060> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#deprecated> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001060> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Wikidata Query Service, DBpedia SPARQL Endpoint, Linked Data Fragments" .
# 
# http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001061
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001061> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001061> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000229> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001061> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "department role"@en .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001061> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Department role is an agent role that is borne by an organizational unit and is realized through carrying out administrative, educational, research, operational, or managerial functions within an organization." .
# 
# http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001062
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001062> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001062> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000229> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001062> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "devision role"@en .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001062> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Division role is an agent role that is borne by an organizational unit and is realized through carrying out administrative, managerial, operational, or research-related functions within an organization." .
# 
# http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001063
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001063> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001063> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000229> .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001063> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "institute role"@en .
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001063> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Institute role is an agent role that is borne by an organization and is realized through conducting, supporting, managing, or promoting research, education, professional activities, or specialized services within one or more domains." .
# 
# http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001064
<http://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/mwo/MWO_0001064> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
