<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000020> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "industry organization role"@en .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000020> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A role inherent in an organization that is realized when promoting, regulating, or supporting industry-specific standards, practices, and collaboration to advance sector development and innovation."@en .
# 
# https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000021
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000021> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000021> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "obsolete workflow"@en .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000021> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#deprecated> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000021> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A plan that specifies a sequence of tasks, processes, or operations, often involving multiple agents, tools, or systems, to achieve a specific goal or produce a desired outcome."@en .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000021> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#editorialNote> "A workflow defines the logical order and dependencies of steps, the roles or entities responsible for each step, and the inputs and outputs required for and produced by each task. It is a realizable entity that can be enacted or executed within a defined context, such as a business process, computational framework, or organizational procedure." .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000021> <https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0010013> "https://github.com/ISE-FIZKarlsruhe/nfdicore/issues/125" .
# 
# https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000022
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000022> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000022> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112> "A journal article, patent application, laboratory notebook, or a book" .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000022> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000310" .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000022> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0100001> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000310> .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000022> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "obsolete document"@en .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000022> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#deprecated> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000022> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A collection of information content entities intended to be understood together as a whole"@en .
# 
# https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000023
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000023> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000023> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000027> .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000023> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ontology"@en .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000023> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An (nfdi) ontology is a data item that coherently represents all components of an ontology, including its versions, variants, modules and other associated artifacts. It is typically denoted by a name and/or an acronym, which is the term we use to communicate about it."@en .
# 
# https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000024
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000024> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000024> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_8000000> .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000024> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "ontology variant"@en .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000024> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An ontology variant represents a self-contained, reusable subset of an ontology that provides a specific functionality while maintaining interoperability with the larger ontology. Typically, an ontology is released in different variants, which makes a variant a release artifact."@en .
# 
# https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0000025
