<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0001022> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A namespace refers to a distinct, unique identifier that is used to distinguish concepts and entities within an ontology from those in other ontologies or systems. It's typically represented as a URL or URI (Uniform Resource Identifier) and ensures that each element within the ontology has a globally unique reference."@en .
