_:genid749 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002351> .
_:genid749 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020004> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> "See editior note of composition to underatand the difference between composition and chemical composition data items.\n\nTo understand the difference between the composition and the composition data item, one has to understand the difference between SDCs and GDCs in BFO. A triple \"material entity has quality compsition\", conveys the fact such quality exists without telling us what are fractions of compounds in this material entity. A triple \"compostion is subject of composition data item\" conveys that there's an information about values of these fractions. Think of comosition data item as a pdf where the composition is documented."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020004> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "composition data item"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020004> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Composition data item is an information content entity that is about composition of a material enity. It has members fraction value specifications which specifiy values of propotions of compounds, which are parts of the material enity."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020004> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Nitric acid solution has quality  composition, and  the composition data item is about this composition.The composition data item has members fraction specifications of nitric acid, e.g., 4 vol.%, and distilled water. These fraction specifications specify value of pure substances of nitric acid and distilled water, respectively. Furthermore, these fraction specifications specify values of relational qualities (volume) proportion of nitric acid and (volume) proportion of distilled water."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020005
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020005> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020005> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020131> .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020005> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "porosity"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020005> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "itensive quality embodiying the fraction of the materials (enclosing) spatial region occupied by pores."@en .
