<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0001070> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "active status"@en .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0001070> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Active Status is a status specification that indicates an entity, process, or project is currently operational, ongoing, or in execution." .
# 
# https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0001071
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0001071> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0001071> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0001056> .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0001071> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "cancelled status"@en .
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0001071> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Cancelled Status is a status specification that indicates an entity, process, or project has been terminated before reaching completion due to internal or external factors." .
# 
# https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0001072
<https://nfdi.fiz-karlsruhe.de/ontology/NFDI_0001072> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
